Getter for boolean if boostrapping was used

Source: R/methods_getters.R, R/class_analysed.R
isBootstrapped-methods.Rd

Returns a boolean if for the analysed object bootstrapping was used to create confidence intervals.

isBootstrapped(obj)

# S4 method for AbstractAnalysedPerturbationData
isBootstrapped(obj)

Arguments

obj

the object for which you want to extract the boolean

Value

returns a boolean.

Examples

 data(rnaiscreen)
 ft <- hm(rnaiscreen)
#> Fitting hierarchical model
 isBootstrapped(ft)
#> [1] FALSE
